id,trigger,conditions,script,text,options,notes
"#RULESET_NAME Draconis",,,,,,
,,,,,,
# Generic Faction Dialogue,,,,,,
XLII_greetingFriendlyCommission,OpenCommLink,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$faction.friendlyToPlayer
XLII_HasDraconisCommission","$menuState = fleetConvMain 0
FireAll PopulateOptions","""Hail, $playerName. I'm $PersonRank $personName, your service record with the $theFaction Navy is impressive. I've heard some flattering nicknames for you. How can we assist?""",,
XLII_greetingFriendly,OpenCommLink,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$faction.friendlyToPlayer","$menuState = fleetConvMain 0
FireAll PopulateOptions","""Transponder's recognized, $playerName. $theFaction has no quarrel with independent operators who've proven themselves reliable."" Their eyes flick to a tactical display. ""State your purpose.""",,
XLII_greetingNeutral,OpenCommLink,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$faction.neutralToPlayer","$menuState = fleetConvMain 0
FireAll PopulateOptions","""This is $PersonRank $personName of $theFaction Navy. Your IFF reads neutral. That can change very quickly, Captain, so let's keep this brief and professional.""",,
XLII_greetingHostileWeaker,OpenCommLink,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$faction.hostileToPlayer
$relativeStrength < 0","$ignorePlayerCommRequests = true 1","""$theFaction Navy to hostile contact: we've fought worse than you in worse conditions. If you're not gone in sixty seconds, we'll add your wreckage to the rest.""","cutCommLink:Cut the comm link",
XLII_greetingHostileWeakerDefiant,OpenCommLink,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$faction.hostileToPlayer
$relativeStrength < 0
$weakerThanPlayerButHolding","$ignorePlayerCommRequests = true 1","""$PersonRank $personName, Alliance Navy."" A measured pause. ""You have tactical superiority. We're not disputing that. But Alliance Command tracks every engagement in this sector, and retaliation doctrine doesn't require us to win, just to make you memorable.""","cutCommLink:Cut the comm link",
XLII_greetingHostileStronger,OpenCommLink,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$faction.hostileToPlayer
$relativeStrength >= 0","$ignorePlayerCommRequests = true 1","""Shouldn't you be running...?"" The officer looks genuinely puzzled.","cutCommLink:Cut the comm link",
"#END Generic Faction Dialogue",,,,,,
,,,,,,
# Generic Commission Dialogue,,,,,,
XLII_CMSNTextRejectHostile,CMSNTextRejectHostile,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""Who the fu - Who is - What - I should kick your fucking ass, who is this?"" There is a brief silence, cut short by the frantic sound of typing. ""Ah, $playerName! I've notified the Department of Internal Security of your presence, leave immediately. Athebyne's scars run deep enough without adding your name to the list.""",,
XLII_CMSNTextHasOther,CMSNTextHasOther,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""Loyalty's a rare commodity out here, and you're fresh out. We've got no room for dual allegiances.""

""That said, if you're serious about joining, resign from $theOtherCommissionFaction. And we'll gladly put your skills to use in $theFaction.""",,
XLII_CMSNTextUnsuited,CMSNTextUnsuited,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""I'm sorry, but you don't meet our criteria for receiving a commission. To put it plainly you're a wildcard, Commander. Shape up your outfit, purge the weak links, then come back. Until then, you're unfit for Draconis colors. However I've noted your request.""",,
XLII_CMSNTextSuitedPart1,CMSNTextSuitedPart1,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""Hmm, yes, you're a suitable candidate. Admiral August will be pleased. We're always short on manpower.""

""Accepting a commission is a serious matter, however. You will be required to fight enemies of $theFaction. You'll be able to resign your commission at any time, though I don't imagine doing so would win you any friends.""",,
XLII_CMSNTextSuitedPart2,CMSNTextSuitedPart2,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""So, how about it? Still want to sign on?""",,
XLII_CMSNTextWelcomePart1,CMSNTextWelcomePart1,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""Oath sworn. Welcome to the fold, Commander. Your IFF's updated - Draconis blue on your scope now.""",,
XLII_CMSNTextWelcomePart2,CMSNTextWelcomePart2,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""Anything else I can do for you?""",,
XLII_CMSNTextChangeMind,CMSNTextChangeMind,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""Cold feet already?"" $personName raises an eyebrow. ""The Sector's full of fence-sitters who think twice when the guns start barking. Fafnir's ghosts don't suffer the hesitant, neither do we. Application withdrawn. If you grow a spine, our doors aren't barred... Yet.""",,
XLII_CMSNResignAskToConfirm,CMSNResignAskToConfirm,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""Resign? After we stamped your papers and handed you the keys to our armory? Commander, that's not how the Alliance works."" $personFirstName pauses their typing to face you. ""$TheFaction needs anyone it can get, and turning your back on us won't be forgotten.""",,
XLII_CMSNResignConfirmed,CMSNResignConfirmed,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"$personFirstName sighs dramatically. ""Fine. Resignation accepted, effective immediately. Your IFF's wiped, access codes revoked.""",,
XLII_CMSNResignCancelled,CMSNResignCancelled,"$faction.id == XLII_draconis",,"""Wise choice, Lieutenant. Knew you had the spine for it. Oath renewed - no hard feelings, just hard lessons.""",,
"#END Generic Commission Dialogue",,,,,,
,,,,,,
# Generic Rep Level Description,,,,,,
XLII_relLevelCooperative,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == COOPERATIVE
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","Fleet Admiral August has personally recognized your contributions to the Alliance. Joint Command has extended full access to military stockpiles and forward operating bases, and even the most security-conscious AIO liaison officers no longer shadow your movements. Alliance Citizens across Fafnir regard you as one of their own - a rare distinction for anyone who didn't endure the Reunification.",,
XLII_relLevelFriendly,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == FRIENDLY
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","Alliance officials have come to regard you as a reliable partner rather than a convenient asset. Port authorities process your docking requests without the usual security theater, and patrol captains are more likely to offer assistance than demand transponder logs. The gratitude of Joint Command translates to meaningful access to military-grade hardware.",,
XLII_relLevelWelcoming,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == WELCOMING
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","Your reputation has reached the attention of mid-level Alliance commanders, several of whom have noted your reliability in official dispatches. System patrols treat your $shipOrFleet as a known quantity rather than a potential threat, and port authorities extend courtesies typically reserved for Alliance-flagged vessels.",,
XLII_relLevelFavorable,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == FAVORABLE
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","Alliance commanders have begun to take note of your activities - favorably, if cautiously. In practice, this means access to surplus military equipment and fewer pointed questions from patrol captains. The institutional paranoia born from the civil war hasn't faded entirely, but you've earned the benefit of the doubt.",,
XLII_relLevelNeutral,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == NEUTRAL
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","To Alliance officials, you're simply another independent operator - neither a threat nor an asset worth cultivating. This is, by local standards, a reasonable position to occupy. The DDA's history has left its leadership wary of outsiders, but not hostile without cause.",,
XLII_relLevelSuspicious,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == SUSPICIOUS
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","Something in your record has drawn scrutiny from Alliance security. Port authorities process your requests with deliberate slowness, and patrol commanders run your transponder against watchlists more often than strictly necessary. You're not unwelcome, but you're certainly not trusted.",,
XLII_relLevelInhospitable,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == INHOSPITABLE
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","Joint Command has flagged your $shipOrFleet as a potential security concern. Port officials find reasons to deny docking requests, and patrol captains interpret their rules of engagement generously when your drives light up on their scopes. The Alliance hasn't declared you an enemy - but they've stopped pretending you might be a friend.",,
XLII_relLevelHostile,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == HOSTILE
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","Alliance patrols are authorized to engage your $shipOrFleet on sight. Markets under DDA control deny you access, and any incident involving your vessels is treated as confirmation of hostile intent. Whatever goodwill you might have once possessed has been thoroughly exhausted.",,
XLII_relLevelVengeful,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == VENGEFUL
$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$player.numColonies == 0
$player.fleetPoints < 120","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","The Alliance has classified you as an active threat to sector stability. Your name circulates in Joint Command briefings alongside pirates, warlords, and other enemies of the fragile peace August built from the ashes of civil war. No patrol captain will hesitate to add your $shipOrFleet to the long list of threats the DDA has ground to dust.",,
XLII_relLevelVengefulFleet,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == VENGEFUL
$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$player.numColonies == 0
$player.fleetPoints >= 120","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","Joint Command regards your $shipOrFleet as one more hostile element in a sector that produces them endlessly. Alliance captains have standing orders to engage and destroy - the same orders they've executed against countless threats since the Reunification. You are not special. You are simply next.",,
XLII_relLevelVengefulPlanet,RelationshipLevelDesc,"$faction.rel == VENGEFUL
$faction.id == XLII_draconis
$player.numColonies > 0","FireAll RelLevelMoreDescription","The Alliance views your growing power as an existential threat to everything the Reunification preserved. Somewhere in Joint Command, planners are assembling a task force with your colonies marked for pacification. The DDA has survived civil war, corporate predation, and worse. They do not intend to let you succeed where those threats failed.",,
"#END Generic Rep Level Description",,,,,,
,,,,,,
# Generic AI Core Donation,,,,,,
XLII_aiCores_turnInOptionSel,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == aiCores_startTurnIn
$faction.id == XLII_draconis","FireAll PopulateCoresTurnInOptions","""We're prepared to pay well for these - better than you'd get selling them quietly elsewhere, and without the legal complications. The Alliance has legitimate research applications for recovered cores. What Hegemony inspectors don't know won't trouble them, or you.""",,
"#END Generic AI Core Donation",,,,,,
,,,,,,
# Fleet Admiral's Store,,,,,,
XLII_admiral_init_greeting,OpenCDE,"$isPerson
$postId == factionLeader
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","AddText ""Establishing connection..."" buttonText
FireBest admiralPickGreeting
ShowPersonVisual","You transmit the comms ID and wait for the system to establish a connection. However, the comms link establishes after a longer delay than typical military protocols demand. When the image resolves, it's deliberately degraded - encryption artifacts dance across a humanoid silhouette, facial features reduced to suggestions of shadow and light.","1:init:Continue",
XLII_admiral_init_not_commissioned,admiralPickGreeting,,,"""Captain."" The voice carries the flat authority of someone accustomed to being obeyed. ""Your reputation precedes you, but reputation alone doesn't grant clearance for what we discuss here.""

A pause. You sense him consulting something off-screen.

""If you're serious about serving the Draconis Defence Alliance, our diplomatic corps can arrange a commission. Standard channels. Until then..."" The distorted figure makes a gesture that might be dismissive, might be regretful. ""I'm afraid we have nothing further to discuss.""

The link cuts before you can respond.","1:dismiss:End the transmission.",
XLII_admiral_init_commissioned,admiralPickGreeting,"XLII_HasDraconisCommission",,,"1:XLII_admiral_init_commissionedTrader:Continue",
XLII_admiral_init_commissionedTrader,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == XLII_admiral_init_commissionedTrader
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","FireAll XLII_AdmiralMainMenu","""Commander $playerLastName."" The distorted visage tilts slightly, as if examining you through the compression grain. What might be satisfaction colors the modulated voice. ""We've been watching your work."" A beat. ""Impressed, I should say.""

He leans forward slightly, the motion causing the encryption to ripple and distort. ""The Draconis Defence Alliance rewards competence. More importantly, we recognize when someone possesses the tactical acumen we need for what's coming.""

Your command console chimes softly - an incoming data packet, heavily encrypted.",,
,,,,,,
