# Fafnir Gate Interactions,,,,,,
XLII_gateOpenDialogStart,OpenInteractionDialog,"$id == XLII_fafnir_gate
!$global.XLII_gateLogRead","ShowDefaultVisual
AddText ""A shattered adamantine ring hangs motionless in the void, its once-perfect curve fractured into jagged arcs.""

AddText ""Twisted structural spars and blackened plating drift in a slow, silent orbit around the broken frame.""

AddText ""What remains of the Gate is cold, dark, and utterly still - a Domain monument reduced to a graveyard of dreams.""",,"1:XLII_gateOpenLogsMenu:Explore
100:defaultLeave:Leave",
XLII_gateOpenDialogFinished,OpenInteractionDialog,"$id == XLII_fafnir_gate
$global.XLII_gateLogRead","ShowDefaultVisual
AddText ""A shattered adamantine ring hangs motionless in the void, its once-perfect curve fractured into jagged arcs.""

AddText ""Twisted structural spars and blackened plating drift in a slow, silent orbit around the broken frame.""

AddText ""What remains of the Gate is cold, dark, and utterly still - a Domain monument reduced to a graveyard of dreams.""",,"100:defaultLeave:Leave",
XLII_gateOpenLogsMenu,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == XLII_gateOpenLogsMenu",,"Closer inspection reveals a skeletal lattice of military emplacements: gun batteries fused into slag, sensor arrays crumpled like paper, armored hab-modules cracked open to vacuum.

Hazard stripes still clings stubbornly to the hull plating beneath layers of micrometeorite scarring and weapons burns.

Faint emergency strobes - long dead - mark the positions where XLII Fleet gun crews once waited, cycle after cycle, for an enemy that never came through.","1:XLII_gateOpenLogs:Send a team to assess the installation
100:defaultLeave:Leave",
XLII_gateOpenLogs,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == XLII_gateOpenLogs",,"Your salvage teams force the frost-sealed airlock of the primary command module. Flashlights sweep across derelict consoles and drifting slats.

Your Ops Chief breaks the silence ""$PlayerSirOrMadam, archives are intact. Something to do with the '42nd Signal Corps' relays, seems untouched since the ring cracked.""

A brief moment as they interface with the databank.

""Gate Vigil logs recovered - Rear Admiral S. Surher's final entry - mid-bombardment.""

""There are more fragments here. Relocation orders to Kori, personnel lists. Permission to extract the full cache?""

Your officers wait for your orders, the soft whine of data recovery filling the bridge.","1:XLII_gateLog1:Continue
100:XLII_gateLeaveOpt:Leave",
XLII_gateLog1,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == XLII_gateLog1","AddTextSmall ""Log Fragment 1 - XLII Signal Corps Standing Order 224-19"" highlight","""Cycle 47 pre-Alliance. Auth: Capt. Emil August, forwarded through Corps Command.""

""'All Signal Corps detachments are hereby detached from line-of-battle duties and assigned to permanent perimeter security and monitoring of Fafnir Gate structure. Primary objective: detect and report any unauthorized hyperspace transit attempt. Secondary objective: prevent physical access by non-cleared personnel.

This assignment is non-negotiable. Resources will be reallocated accordingly.

Endorsement appended by Lt. Cmdr. J. Halvorsen, Signal Corps:

""Understood the strategic logic on paper. Still feels like punishment duty. We're bleeding hull plating at Athebyne's Lagrange points while half the corps sits on cold alloy watching a ring that hasn't twitched since the Collapse. August must know something we don't. Or he's finally lost it.""'","2:XLII_gateLog2:Continue",
XLII_gateLog2,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == XLII_gateLog2","AddTextSmall ""Log Fragment 2 - Field Engineering Log, Attempt Series 12-47"" highlight","""Cycle 49 pre-Alliance. Auth: Lt. Mara Velas, Field Engineering Lead.""

""'Attempt 47 concluded 03:14 shipboard. Full power shunt through primary manifold coupling. Ring returned to quiescent state within 0.8 seconds. No aperture formation, no phase excursion, no manifold breach.

Same result as Attempt 46. And 45. And every attempt back to 12.

However: return signal consistent across all attempts. Three discrete hyperwave pulses, 1.7-second spacing, identical modulation envelope. Subcarrier contains structured data we cannot yet parse. It responds to our probe strength - louder input yields louder reply.

It is not an echo. It is a handshake.

Recommendation: cease active attempts until we can fabricate better decoding hardware. Morale note: crew has started calling the anomaly 'the patient one.' Not sure I like the nickname.'""","3:XLII_gateLog3:Continue",
XLII_gateLog3,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == XLII_gateLog3","AddTextSmall ""Log Fragment 3 - Redeployment Directive, Eyes-Only"" highlight","""Cycle 51 pre-Alliance. Auth: Adm. Emil August, countersigned AIO precursor cell.""

""'Effective immediately: all Signal Corps assets under designation 'Gatewatch' are to cease operations at Fafnir Gate and redeploy subsurface, Kori primary grid, reference Alpha-7 / Theta-9.

New primary objective: secure, stabilize, and establish interface protocols with Domain-era megastructure; codeword designation: [OCTANTIS].

All previous Gate monitoring logs are to be archived under maximum encryption and physically transferred to Kori vault. No further active interrogation of the Gate permitted. Demolition charges remain on standby per prior order.

Personal addendum, August: ""The answers are under Kori. That is where the war will be decided now.""'","4:XLII_gateLog4:Continue",
XLII_gateLog4,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == XLII_gateLog4","AddTextSmall ""Log Fragment 4 - Internal Transition Memorandum"" highlight
AddStoryPoints 1
BeginMission BlindEyeQuestMission
$global.XLII_gateLogRead = true","""Cycle 52 pre-Alliance. Auth: precursor cell, later designated Alliance Intelligence Office.""

""'Signal Corps detachment Gatewatch formally stood down. Surviving personnel and technical assets folded into new standing formation: Alliance Intelligence Section (provisional) under Rear Admiral S. Surher's oversight.

Mission parameters redefined: - Acquisition, integration, and operational employment of [OCTANTIS]-derived computational systems. - Evaluation and controlled implementation of AI-core augmentation protocols previously prohibited under Sector norms. - Protection of all related programs from external compromise (Hegemony, Persean League, Tri-Tachyon, Luddic elements). - Elimination or reorientation of personnel who represent unacceptable risk to operational security.

From this cycle forward, the Section answers only to unified command authority. Taboos are suspended for the duration of the emergency - which is now declared permanent.

Final line, unsigned but cipher-matched to August: ""You are no longer watchers. You are keepers. And you shall keep what must never be loosed upon the Sector... or what must be loosed only by our hand.""'

They tap the console once more, locking the slate.

""Whatever [OCTANTIS] actually is... it didn't come through the Gate. It was already here. And it's been talking to them.""

A beat of silence on the bridge.

""Orders, Captain?""","100:defaultLeave:Leave",
"#END Fafnir Gate Interactions",,,,,,
,,,,,,
# Blind Eye Quest,,,,,,
,,,,,,
# Act 0 - The Logs,,,,,,
XLII_gate_logs_discuss_sel,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == XLII_gate_logs_discuss
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","FireBest XLII_GateLogsBranch",,,"Routes to full gate logs conversation"
XLII_gate_logs_branch_full,XLII_GateLogsBranch,,"FireAll XLII_GateLogsQuestions","""Well you've read the logs."" A measured pause. ""You know more than most officers who've served under me.""

A silence. You hear something - keys, or equipment - before he continues.

""Certain precautions are required for this channel, given what we're discussing.""

""The brief the Office gave me and what the Office actually knows are not the same document. I'll tell you what I can. Which is less than you'll want.""",,
XLII_gate_logs_deflect_leave,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_deflect_leave
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","AdjustRepPerson XLII_fleet_admiral_emil COOPERATIVE 5
$global.XLII_gateLogDeflected = true
EndConversation","""Good."" A brief pause. ""And Commander - the Alliance doesn't forget the people who handle information correctly. Safe travels.""

The link closes cleanly.",,
XLII_gate_logs_deflect_press,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_press
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","$global.XLII_gateLogDeflected = true
EndConversation","""Commander. I strongly suggest sealing your lips."" The voice is flat. ""We shall continue this another time.""

The link terminates.",,
XLII_gate_logs_q_base,XLII_GateLogsQuestions,"$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil",,,,
XLII_gate_logs_q1_opt,XLII_GateLogsQuestions,"$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil
!$global.XLII_logQ1Complete",,,"1:gate_logs_q1:Why did you stop trying to open the Gate?",
XLII_gate_logs_q2_opt,XLII_GateLogsQuestions,"$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil
!$global.XLII_logQ2Complete",,,"2:gate_logs_q2:Why does the AIO have so much control?",
XLII_gate_logs_q3_opt,XLII_GateLogsQuestions,"$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil
!$global.XLII_logQ3Complete",,,"3:gate_logs_q3:What did you find under Kori?",
XLII_gate_logs_q_continue,XLII_GateLogsQuestions,"$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil
$global.XLII_logQ1Complete
$global.XLII_logQ2Complete
$global.XLII_logQ3Complete",,,"10:gate_logs_finale:I think I understand the shape of it.",
XLII_gate_logs_q_return,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_q_return
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","FireAll XLII_GateLogsQuestions",,,"Loop-back from each question answer"
XLII_gate_logs_q1_sel,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_q1
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","$global.XLII_logQ1Complete = true","""Because the Gate was never the source."" A pause. ""The pings stopped the moment we cracked Kori's surface. Whatever was responding - it didn't come through gates. It was already here.""

The encryption holds. He doesn't move.

""The Gate was a receiver. A way of asking whether something was listening. Once we understood that, continuing at the Gate was redundant. The conversation had already moved.""","1:gate_logs_q_return:Continue",
XLII_gate_logs_q2_sel,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_q2
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","$global.XLII_logQ2Complete = true","""I gave them a mandate and they filled it."" His tone lays flat. No defensiveness. ""Counterintelligence. Then signals. Then guarding Kori. Each expansion seemed reasonable at the time, inside the emergency we were managing.""

A brief silence.

""By the time I understood what they'd become, reversing it would have required options I no longer had. The Office knows too much. The Office does too much. And the Alliance depends on both."" He pauses. ""Some blindspots are chosen, Commander. You'll learn that if you haven't already.""","1:gate_logs_q_return:Continue",
XLII_gate_logs_q3_sel,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_q3
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","$global.XLII_logQ3Complete = true","""Our key to survival."" A pause. ""That's what I told myself.""

He shifts. The encryption distorts around the motion.

""A Domain-era computational device. Designated OCTANTIS. Built to coordinate colonial infrastructure across multiple systems - resource allocation, logistics, production planning. Never finished. Sealed when the Collapse severed its purpose.""

He is quiet for a moment.

""Then the Office woke it."" Another pause, heavier. ""And that's where the fog of war begins. I know the outline. The Office knows the rest.""","1:gate_logs_q_return:Continue",
XLII_gate_logs_finale_sel,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_finale
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil",,"The line is quiet for a moment. Longer than it needs to be.

""You've heard more than most, Commander."" His voice is measured and deliberate. ""Let me ask you something in return.""

A pause.

""Given everything you know - the Gate, Kori, the Office, what was necessary to keep this system alive - what would you have done in my position?""","1:gate_logs_ans_same:I would've done the same as you.
2:gate_logs_ans_understand:I would've tried harder to understand it first.
3:gate_logs_ans_aio:I wouldn't have let the AIO get that far.
4:gate_logs_ans_athebyne:I would've bombed Athebyne again.
5:gate_logs_ans_dontknow:I don't know.",
XLII_gate_logs_ans_same,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_ans_same
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil",,"""I'm so surrounded by yes-men that it is hard to believe it, but given the benefit of doubt.""

He is still for a moment.

""Good..."" The word lands without inflection. ""That's the correct answer, and the honest one.""

A pause.

""Survival doesn't come with clean choices. Anyone who tells you otherwise has never been responsible for something that cannot be allowed to fail.""

""I'm glad we understand each other.""","1:gate_logs_closing:It's been an instructive conversation.",
XLII_gate_logs_ans_understand,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_ans_understand
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil",,"""Yes."" He doesn't dismiss it. ""You might have.""

A pause.

""I've had that thought myself. In the years after Kori went active - what might we have learned, if we'd moved more slowly. If we'd been less desperate.""

The encrypted silhouette is still.

""But the war didn't give us time for philosophy, Commander. It rarely does. We understood enough to survive. I'm not certain understanding more would have made us safer.""","1:gate_logs_closing:It's been an instructive conversation.",
XLII_gate_logs_ans_aio,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_ans_aio
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil",,"""Neither would I."" The voice is dry. ""In principle. The problem with principle is that it requires you to identify the line before you've crossed it.""

A pause.

""The Office was useful. Then it was necessary. Then it was irreplaceable. Each transition seemed logical at the time. The war makes everything seem logical."" He is quiet for a moment. ""If you find a way to draw that line clearly, Commander, let me know. I've been looking for it for thirty years.""","1:gate_logs_closing:It's been an instructive conversation.",
XLII_gate_logs_ans_athebyne,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_ans_athebyne
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil",,"He stares at you for a moment. Then he laughs.

Brief. Unguarded. He doesn't appear to have expected it any more than you did.

A pause.

The silence that follows is almost thoughtful.

""...Right.""

He moves on as if it didn't happen.","1:gate_logs_closing:It's been an instructive conversation.",
XLII_gate_logs_ans_dontknow,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_ans_dontknow
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil",,"""Good."" A pause. ""That's a more honest answer than most.""

He is quiet.

""Neither did I, at the time. That's the truth of it. The Gate responded, and we followed the thread because we were losing and we needed anything we could use. And we accepted it because the alternative was starvation and slow defeat."" The encrypted silhouette is still. ""I made decisions under uncertainty and they kept the Alliance alive. I don't know if they were right. But I know they were necessary.""

A brief pause.

""That distinction gets heavier every year.""","1:gate_logs_closing:It's been an instructive conversation.",
XLII_gate_logs_closing,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == gate_logs_closing
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","$global.XLII_logConversationComplete = true
EndConversation","""Likewise, Commander.""

He keys something. The encrypted image holds for a moment, then clears.

""We'll be in touch.""

The link closes.",,
"#END Act 0 - The Logs",,,,,,
