XLII_elias_init,OpenCDE,"$isPerson
$tag:XLII_elias_korrin
$global.XLII_transponderVerified
!$global.XLII_blindEyeMissionActive
!$global.XLII_blindEyeDeclined
!$global.XLII_ringPortTaken","ShowPersonVisual
FireAll XLII_EliasIntro",,,"First contact with Elias. Fires intro scene."
XLII_elias_intro_continue,XLII_EliasIntro,,,"The feed resolves after a moment - no ident header, no station routing tag. A young man, background dark. He looks at the pickup. ""Commander."" A pause. ""Korrin.""","1:elias_continue:Continue.",
XLII_elias_briefing,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == elias_continue","FireAll XLII_EliasOptions","'You received the note?"" He follows up before you can answer. ""Good. Apologies for the secrecy - this operation is too important to risk on sloppiness.""

""I've been told to brief you on our operation, so to cut it short - the Fleet Admiral sent me to prepare the station for a change of hands. The operational specifics are recent.""

""August wants Ring-Port back, but not via our usual channels. And until now we haven't been able to commit Alliance assets without AIO oversight, and the Office's involvement would mean documentation, a review and secure process, and a multi-cycle delay while the Office investigates every nook and cranny of this facility before they even considered a direct assault."" A pause. ""You are not subject to that oversight.""",,"Briefing text. Fires XLII_EliasOptions to populate Q&A and accept/decline choices."
XLII_elias_opt_why,XLII_EliasOptions,"!$global.XLII_elias_askedWhy",,,"1:elias_why:Why Ring-Port? Why now?",
XLII_elias_opt_occupants,XLII_EliasOptions,"!$global.XLII_elias_askedOccupants",,,"2:elias_occupants:The station's current occupants.",
XLII_elias_opt_accept,XLII_EliasOptions,,,,"3:elias_accept:I'll do it.",
XLII_elias_opt_decline,XLII_EliasOptions,,,,"4:elias_decline:Not yet.",
XLII_elias_why,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == elias_why","$global.XLII_elias_askedWhy = true
FireAll XLII_EliasOptions","""Two main reasons, firstly, the logistical output of Ring-Port is not insignificant, and we need all the help we can get. Secondly, it's a matter of optics; we may be a small fish in a large pond, but this reflects poorly on the Alliance for not being able to take back such an important asset. Those are the official reasons, anyway; in reality, we need the free operating space to work without oversight. August has been assembling a contingent of those loyal to him and wants to seize control of the Office.""

""The plan is straightforward. When the station changes hands, the AIO will arrive quickly after. That is expected. But our people are already embedded here - dock workers, transit staff, maintenance contractors, the list goes on - but the important detail is we've already prepared and secured this station before the AIO can sterilise it. If Alliance personnel hold the facility before the Office arrives, they hold it on the Admiral's terms.""

A moment's pause as Korrin leans back, as he takes a moment for himself.

""The timing was mine to judge. I sent the signal when the station's current commander was between reliable subordinates. This window is narrow.""",,
XLII_elias_occupants,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == elias_occupants","$global.XLII_elias_askedOccupants = true
FireAll XLII_EliasOptions","He nods as he considers the question.

""Well, originally, First Fleet veterans who refused integration after the armistice. The originals are mostly old now. Their children and the people those children trained are running the operation now.""

""They are technically proficient. They have survived in a hostile system on ingenuity and deterrence. They understand that the Alliance cannot absorb them without political consequence."" He stops there. ""But this operation isn't about petty revenge. Besides, their lives will be better under Alliance Control...""

He trails off on the last sentence, clearly not sold on his own words. But he catches himself.

""The important bit is they are proficient but underfunded fighters, Commander.""",,
XLII_elias_accept,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == elias_accept
XLII_HasMarinesForAssault","FireAll XLII_EliasConfirmOptions","He scans his terminal display. ""That's what I need to hear. My people are staged - the watch rotation on the cargo lock is clear, the maintenance window holds for another six hours. You have a window and the force to use it."" He closes the feed channel. ""The moment you launch, I'm inside with you.""",,"Player has enough marines - show launch confirmation."
XLII_elias_accept_nomines,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == elias_accept
!XLII_HasMarinesForAssault","FireAll XLII_EliasNeedMarinesOptions","He shakes his head. ""Not yet. The garrison runs thick for its size - First Fleet veterans who've spent two decades hardening that station against exactly this kind of assault. Five hundred marines minimum, and that's assuming everything I've arranged goes right. Come back when you have the numbers.""",,"Player lacks marines - show reminder."
XLII_elias_decline,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == elias_decline","$global.XLII_blindEyeDeclined = true
EndConversation","""Noted..."" He opens the datapad again. ""I'll be here.""",,"Sets XLII_blindEyeDeclined. Return dialog remains available."
