XLII_admiral_debrief_opt,XLII_AdmiralMainMenu,"$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil
$global.XLII_ringPortTaken
!$global.XLII_blindEyeComplete",,,"1:ring_port_debrief:About Ring-Port.","Appears in August's main menu once after assault. Disappears when blindEyeComplete."
XLII_admiral_debrief_init,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == ring_port_debrief
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","FireBest XLII_AugustDebriefOpening",,,"Entry point. FireBest routes to the correct performance-tier opening."
XLII_august_debrief_open_precise,XLII_AugustDebriefOpening,"$global.XLII_raidPrecise","FireAll XLII_AugustDebriefContent","""Clean operation. Precise. However, don't mistake that for a compliment without conditions.""",,"Precise path: under 20% marines lost."
XLII_august_debrief_open_costly,XLII_AugustDebriefOpening,"$global.XLII_raidCostly","FireAll XLII_AugustDebriefContent","""The casualty count is significant."" He does not minimize it. ""But Ring-Port is held. That was the objective, good job.""",,"Costly path: over 50% marines lost."
XLII_august_debrief_open_accept,XLII_AugustDebriefOpening,,"FireAll XLII_AugustDebriefContent","""Ring-Port is secured. The count is filed."" A pause. ""We have what we came for.""",,"Fallback path: 20-50% marines lost."
XLII_august_debrief_beat3risky,XLII_AugustDebriefContent,"$global.XLII_beat3Risky",,"""I heard there were civilian causalities in the lower decks."" A pause as he leans back, static darting across his figure, as he makes a movement that can only be considered smoking. ""This is an issue Korrin will have to fix. He has had worse. But he will carry it regardless. This does, however, reflect poorly on all of us.""",,"Fires if Beat 3 was RISKY (marines pushed through civilians)."
XLII_august_debrief_beat5sp,XLII_AugustDebriefContent,"$global.XLII_beat5SP",,"""The inner sanctum's surrender was formal - observed, documented, clean under the Transit Accords."" A pause. ""That was the outcome I was hoping for.""",,"Fires if Beat 5 was SP (formal surrender under Transit Accords)."
XLII_august_debrief_beat5risky,XLII_AugustDebriefContent,"$global.XLII_beat5Risky",,"""No prisoners from the inner sanctum. I knew some of them, personally, they were not going to surrender to a foreign commission. Not after twenty years of spitting in my face. I had accounted for the possibility. Clean work.""",,"Fires if Beat 5 was RISKY (breach and clear)."
XLII_august_debrief_beat5safe,XLII_AugustDebriefContent,"$global.XLII_beat5Safe",,"""The inner sanctum's veterans - most of them - are in custody. That is workable. Less clean than a formal surrender. Korrin will manage the transition regardless.""",,"Fires if Beat 5 was SAFE (negotiated surrender, mixed result)."
XLII_august_debrief_korrin,XLII_AugustDebriefContent,,,"He keys something on the console - not looking at you now.

""I have your transfer ready, $global.XLII_raidCreditRewardFormatted credits, I'm sure you'll appreciate. The Alliance does not forget its contracts.""","1:debrief_elias:About Korrin.
2:debrief_ack:Understood.","Always fires last. Fixed Korrin paragraph and close options."
XLII_august_debrief_ack,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == debrief_ack
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","XLII_DeliverRaidReward
$global.XLII_blindEyeComplete = true
FireAll XLII_AdmiralMainMenu",,,
XLII_august_debrief_elias,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == debrief_elias
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","FireAll XLII_AugustDebriefElias","A pause that runs a half-second longer than it needs to, you could almost mistake it as a sigh.

""That place was personal to him; that's why he was there, but that's not the relevant fact. He'll be fine, Commander.""

He trails off, nothing in his expression. Nothing in his voice.",,
XLII_august_debrief_elias_text,XLII_AugustDebriefElias,,,,"1:debrief_elias_close:Understood.",
XLII_august_debrief_elias_close,DialogOptionSelected,"$option == debrief_elias_close
$tag:XLII_fleet_admiral_emil","XLII_DeliverRaidReward
$global.XLII_blindEyeComplete = true
FireAll XLII_AdmiralMainMenu",,,
"#END Act 4 - August Debrief",,,,,,
,,,,,,
# Act 4b - August External Capture Debrief,,,,,,
